This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image feature detection, homography estimation, and image synthesis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture design for deep learning, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of masks and outlier rejection, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with robotics and motion estimation, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper mentions the use of a comprehensive dataset, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
